race.comment: WEBEJAMIN (6) drops back in grade today and has finally drawn a good barrier. Covered ground in the run when a plugging eighth at Randwick in Midway company. Goes well on her home track and shapes as the value play. SQUEEZEBOX (2) win record hardly excites but has his hoof on the till fifth-up. Well supported to start fav when a plugging third over 1500m here behind Miss Hvar. Proven at the trip and goes close. MAGIC PHAROAH (8) mare in form close to a win. Surged late from back in the field when third over 2000m at this track. Worth thought on the backup. GWENDIE (10) blinkers come off and the winkers go on after disappointing when fifth over 1500m at this track. Trip suits and don't dismiss.
